Based on these above studies of PPy and CQDs/PPy composite electrodes, the CQDs/PPy-30 composite electrode demonstrates the best overall electrochemical performance. Thus, a flexible ASSS was fabricated with two CQDs/PPy-30 composite electrodes by using LiCl-PVA gel electrolyte as separator. Fig. 6
                        (A) shows the CV curves of the as-fabricated flexible ASSSs at various scan rates from 5 to 50mVs−1. The nearly rectangular-shape mirror image of CVs reveals that the CQDs/PPy supercapacitor has ideal capacitive behavior. Additionally, even at high scan rate, the CV curves still maintained the quasi-rectangular shape, implying the fast charge-discharge property of the CQDs/PPy supercapacitor. The high-rate performance of this device can be attributed to the “nano-islands” structure of the CQD/PPy composite film, which can improve the ion/electron transportion. The charge-discharge curves of this CQDs/PPy supercapacitor at different current densities of 0.2, 0.5, 1, 2 and 4mAcm−2 are displayed in Fig. 6(B). Interestingly, all the GCD curves exhibit a symmetrical triangle shapes, indicating a high degree of reversibility during charge and discharge process. Meanwhile, the rate performance of PPy and CQDs/PPy composite against the current density is depicted in Fig. 6(C). Although the areal capacitance of CQDs/PPy composite (315mFcm−2, corresponding to specific capacitance of 308Fg−1) at a current density of 0.2mAcm−2 is smaller than the PPy based supercapacitor (434mFcm−2), the better rate capability of CQDs/PPy supercapacitor (38.7%) when the current density is increased by 40 times is comparable with that the pure PPy (5.1%). We can be attributed to the different nanostructure of PPy and CQDs/PPy composite: PPy without CQDs will constitute denser film on the surface of SSMW under the same electrodeposition time (see the above SEM images of the pure PPy and CQDs/PPy composite), so at a low current density (0.2mAcm−2) the PPy supercapacitor demonstrates larger areal capacitance. However, with the increasing of current density, the porous nanostructure of CQDs/PPy composite would provide more pathways to promote the LiCl ions from the electrolyte to the inner of CQDs/PPy composite, leading to a complete insertion reaction. In addition, the obtained specific capacitance values are superior to those previously reported, such as PPy/GO composite (152mFcm−2, Ref. [29]) and PPy-GO/CNT (142.2mFcm−2, Ref. [33]), table S1 compared the specific capacitance (Cs
                        ) and areal capacitance (Ca
                        ) of CQDs/PPy composite supercapacitor with previous reports.
